<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: POWAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A brush fire broke out Sunday afternoon in hilly terrain in the Twin Peaks area 
of Poway, according to firefighter Scott Kelly of the Poway Fire Department. 
</P>
<P>
All units of the Poway Fire Department were called to the 5- to 6-acre area and 
were assisted by trucks from the San Diego Fire Department, Kelly said. 
</P>
<P>
The fire broke out shortly before 2 p.m. Sunday and firefighters fought the 
blaze for about an hour and 20 minutes, he said. There were no injuries. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly said investigators are attempting to determine whether the fire was set 
by an arsonist. 
</P>
