TOREROS WIN THEIR CONFERENCE FINALE IN BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dan McAdoo's one-out single to left field scored Chuck Graham from second base 
in the bottom of the 10th inning to give the University of San Diego a 7-6 
victory over visiting Nevada Reno in the Toreros' final Western Conference 
Athletic Conference baseball game Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The Toreros scored four runs in the eighth inning to take a 6-5 lead, but 
Nevada Reno tied the score in the ninth. 
</P>
<P>
Jim Keen went three for four with a triple for USD (20-30-1 overall, 5-17 in 
the conference). Tony Battilega (4-5) was the winner in relief. Nevada Reno is 
26-26, 9-11. 
