<P>
FOUR KILLED IN FIERY CRASH OF SMALL PLANE IN GEORGIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By from Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DAHLONEGA, Ga. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Four people, including an infant, were killed when their small plane crashed 
and burst into flames in a mountainous region, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
One passenger, a young girl, survived the crash Saturday, authorities said. She 
was listed in stable condition. The cause of the crash was under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
