had design flaws that made them dangerous. "Honda is extremely disappointed in 
the verdict and believes it is excessive and unwarranted," Kurt Antonius of 
American Honda Motor Co. Inc. of Gardena, Calif., said Saturday. "We will 
pursue all of the appropriate legal remedies, including appeal." 
