<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOT LINE IS SOLD TO SWISS-OWNED FIRM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
UPPER SADDLE RIVER, N.J. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The hot line, the link set up between Washington and Moscow more than 25 years 
ago to reduce the risk of an accidental war, has fallen into foreign hands. 
</P>
<P>
The hot line was part of a division Western Union Corp. sold last week to 
Swiss-owned Tele-Columbus USA of New York for $56 million as part of a 
reorganization, Western Union said. 
</P>
<P>
Western Union kept the division's telex and international cablegram businesses. 
</P>
<P>
Tele-Columbus is owned by Motor-Columbus AG, a telecommunications and cable 
television company based in Baden, Switzerland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
