ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MODJESKA CANYON; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECT HELD IN SLAYING OF MAN FOUND IN ROAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A suspect has been arrested in the murder of an Anaheim man whose body was 
found last week near the entrance of Modjeska Canyon, the Orange County 
Sheriff's Department said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Lt. Harold Schaffroth said Mark Edward Ross, 26, of Anaheim was arrested 
Saturday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
He said Ross is being held at Orange County jail on suspicion of the murder of 
Thomas Kuehn, 22, of Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
Kuehn's fully clothed body was found by a passer-by about 4 p.m. Wednesday near 
Modjeska Canyon Road and Santiago Canyon Road, Schaffroth said. 
</P>
<P>
An autopsy determined that Kuehn had died of multiple gunshot wounds, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Schaffroth said no details of Ross' arrest, including a possible motive for the 
murder, were available Sunday. 
</P>
