<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ANAHEIM; 
</P>
<P>
CONFERENCE ON CHILDREN WILL OPEN ON THURSDAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Marian Wright Edelman, founder and president of the Children's Defense Fund, 
will deliver the keynote address at noon Thursday for the 67th annual 
conference of the Assn. of Junior Leagues Inc. in Anaheim. 
</P>
<P>
The 3-day conference, titled "Advancing a Children's Agenda," will focus solely 
on children's issues, such as the crisis in the foster-care system, 
homelessness and hunger, intervention in child abuse, the declining status of 
children in American, promoting self-esteem through art, and the role of 
volunteers in promoting federal and state action. 
</P>
<P>
In collaboration with the Children's Defense Fund, a national advocacy 
organization for families and children, Junior Leagues have worked for child 
welfare reform, homeless families, adolescent pregnancy prevention and child 
care. 
</P>
<P>
Other speakers will include Jeanette Dunckel, chair of the Foster 
Care/Adoptions Policy Board, California Children's Lobby and the Children's 
Research Institute of California, and Cynthia Robbins, executive director of 
Children NOW, a child advocacy organization in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
The conference will be held at the Anaheim Hilton and Towers, 777 W. Convention 
Way in Anaheim.CountywideCentennial Pin Sets to Be Sold by County 
</P>
<P>
Beginning Thursday, the the Orange County public information office will be 
selling limited-edition sets of six Orange County Centennial pins for $30. 
</P>
<P>
The sets are glass enclosed in wood frames and contain five previously issued 
pins and a sixth pin depicting the centennial symbol. 
</P>
<P>
The other five pins depict such landmarks as the Old County Courthouse in Santa 
Ana, the Huntington Beach Pier, the San Juan Capistrano Mission, Knott's Berry 
Farm, Disneyland and Anaheim Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
The sets may be purchased at the Public Information Office in the Hall of 
Administration on 10 Civic Center Plaza in Santa Ana. between 8 a.m. and 5 p.m. 
during the week. There is a two-set limit per person. 
</P>
<P>
Also on sale is "The Complete Guide to Orange County," which includes 
historical information, lists of cultural attractions, cities, government 
offices, parks, harbors and beaches. The guide is sold for $2.50.Huntington 
BeachMental Health Talk Scheduled for May 10 
</P>
<P>
Mental health care will be discussed on May 10 by Wendy Kelley of the South 
Coast Alliance for the Mentally Ill. The title of her talk is, "Mental Health 
in California -- Where Do We Stand?." 
</P>
<P>
Kelley will speak before the Democratic Club of West Orange County at 7 p.m. in 
the Talbert Room of the Huntington Beach Library, Talbert Avenue and Golden 
West Street. 
</P>
<P>
Kelly has been a teacher for the Newport-Mesa Unified School District and the 
UC Irvine Women's Opportunity Center and has been board president of the South 
Coast Alliance for the Mentally Ill. The alliance is a volunteer organization 
which acts as an advocate for the mentally ill. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting is free and open to the public. For information, call 898-1882. 
</P>
