<TEXT>
<P>
A Finnish collector and Beatles fan bought a ticket to ride in the style of the 
Fab Four when he bid $234,000 at Christie's for a white Mercedes Benz limousine 
that belonged to late Beatle John Lennon. The four-door, black-seated 
limousine, custom built for Lennon in 1970, later belonged to fellow Beatle 
George Harrison before being sold to Mary Wilson, an original member of the 
Supremes pop group. Two hand-written verses of a poem by Lennon, illustrated 
with a sketch, netted $5,450. A rainbow-colored 1965 Bentley automobile that 
once ferried John Lennon and the other Beatles through the streets of London 
also goes on the auction block in June. The car, now owned by a New York 
couple, is expected to fetch between $800,000 and millionClaudia Puig 
